    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1471169379" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1471169379" />
    <a title="Melissa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1266570-melissa"><img alt="Melissa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450935170p2/1266570.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1471169379?book_show_action=true">Dec 17, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melissa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melissa" href="/user/show/1266570-melissa">Melissa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1471169379" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18165398790505249845">You know that line in the Carly Simon song about how melodrama doesn&apos;t make her weep anymore? Well, I guess it does still make me weep. Or at least get a little teary-eyed. This book was an emotional roller-coaster ride, featuring six years of heartwrenching drama for the hero and heroine before their HEA. I enjoyed it a lot.<br/><br/>Penelope Williamson is a really good writer. She and Patricia Gaffney have been my best discoveries of the year by far. Both make me feel wrung out and emotionally exhausted</span>
  <span id="freeText18165398790505249845" style="display:none">You know that line in the Carly Simon song about how melodrama doesn't make her weep anymore? Well, I guess it does still make me weep. Or at least get a little teary-eyed. This book was an emotional roller-coaster ride, featuring six years of heartwrenching drama for the hero and heroine before their HEA. I enjoyed it a lot.<br /><br />Penelope Williamson is a really good writer. She and Patricia Gaffney have been my best discoveries of the year by far. Both make me feel wrung out and emotionally exhausted by the time I finish their books. I mean this as a huge compliment! Nothing beats having the heart ripped out of you by a long, sweeping, well-written historical romance. Unlike Carly, I <i>have</i> got time for the pain. ;)</span>
  <a data-text-id="18165398790505249845" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


