<div id="review_2588570827" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2588570827" />
    <a title="Amy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47752474-amy"><img alt="Amy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607174013p2/47752474.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2588570827?book_show_action=true">Nov 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amy" href="/user/show/47752474-amy">Amy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2588570827" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2845330738214436958">A long story that made me sigh at times due to the H&amp;H unable to get their HEA when *I* wanted it, but I truly loved both characters. Yes, there is a lot of heartache in this novel, but also a lot of love and passion. I liked that this was a solid story in a different vein than the &apos;normal&apos; romance story; that being the Hero was trying to fulfill his vision and dream of a world of steam engines and railroads. He was full of honor and pride and duty. The heroine was full of love, patience and sac</span>
  <span id="freeText2845330738214436958" style="display:none">A long story that made me sigh at times due to the H&amp;H unable to get their HEA when *I* wanted it, but I truly loved both characters. Yes, there is a lot of heartache in this novel, but also a lot of love and passion. I liked that this was a solid story in a different vein than the 'normal' romance story; that being the Hero was trying to fulfill his vision and dream of a world of steam engines and railroads. He was full of honor and pride and duty. The heroine was full of love, patience and sacrifice. Both very good for each other!<br /><br />Very much worth taking the time to read and enjoy!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2845330738214436958" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


