    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/700798771?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Copper78" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Copper78" href="/user/show/19366821-copper78">Copper78</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19366821-copper78?shelf=historical">historical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer700798771" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15616029052465372899">I am a self professed romance-junkie. I read several genres, historical being one of my favorites. I read a crazy number of books each month, always looking for that elusive story that will truly move me. Very few books actually do this. I have a list of a few all time favorites and The Outsider by Penelope Williamson is at the top of that list. I have read several other books by PW and had yet to come across the same magic she created in The Outsider. Until now. I absolutely loved Once in a Blu</span>
  <span id="freeText15616029052465372899" style="display:none">I am a self professed romance-junkie. I read several genres, historical being one of my favorites. I read a crazy number of books each month, always looking for that elusive story that will truly move me. Very few books actually do this. I have a list of a few all time favorites and The Outsider by Penelope Williamson is at the top of that list. I have read several other books by PW and had yet to come across the same magic she created in The Outsider. Until now. I absolutely loved Once in a Blue Moon. The characters, their motivations, the dialogue, the setting, the emotions are all so well written that I was truly transported and lived the trials and tribulations along with Jessalyn and McCady. These characters and their chemistry just jumped off the page. There was no denying their attraction or their "rightness" for one another. So when the story makes some surprising twists and turns, I was devastated. Just beside myself. Thankfully, instead of throwing out the book and crying myself to sleep, I trusted Ms. Williamson and she did not disappoint. In fact, of the several love stories of hers that I've read, Once in a Blue Moon is probably the most romantic. All her stories have heartache, angst and a somewhat melancholy feel at times, but this one actually has some seriously swoon-worthy romance, and steamier love scenes than many of her other books.<br /><br />I can't recommend this book enough, it will make you laugh, cry, feel betrayed, feel vindicated, and give you memorable characters you'll love so much. When Williamson is on point, nobody does it better.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15616029052465372899" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


